# =============================================================================
# APPLICATION PROTOCOL (Usage Instructions)
# =============================================================================
APPLICATION:
  Frequency: Continuous monitoring, on-demand repair
  Timing: 
    - Detection Phase: Real-time (< 100ms latency)
    - Diagnosis Phase: 1-5 seconds
    - Repair Phase: 1-5 minutes
    - Validation Phase: 30-60 seconds
  
  Method:
    1. DETECT: Autognostic engine continuously monitors system health
    2. DIAGNOSE: Root cause analysis with impact assessment
    3. ISOLATE: Quarantine affected components to prevent spread
    4. REPAIR: Apply appropriate healing mechanism:
       - Rollback for state corruption
       - Rebuild for pattern damage
       - Refresh for knowledge issues
    5. VALIDATE: Comprehensive post-repair testing
    6. LEARN: Document incident and update prevention patterns
  
  Integration:
    - Service Daemon: repair.daemon.scm (runs continuously)
    - MLOps Pipeline: Integrated with CI/CD workflows
    - Alert System: PagerDuty, Slack, email notifications
    - Metrics: Grafana dashboard for repair analytics

# =============================================================================
# EXPECTED RESULTS (Performance Targets)
# =============================================================================
EXPECTED_RESULTS:
  - Detection Accuracy: 95%+ anomaly detection rate
  - False Positive Rate: < 5% incorrect alerts
  - Repair Success Rate: 90%+ automated resolution
  - Mean Time to Detect (MTTD): < 2 minutes
  - Mean Time to Repair (MTTR): < 10 minutes
  - System Availability: 99.9% during healing
  - Scar Visibility: Minimal lasting impact on performance

